description: Recently sold: $111,000. Beautiful building with lots of character and charm, built in 1929. Beautiful re-finished hardwood floors.  Wonderful view of downtown skyline! beautiful hardwood floors, lots of closet space! Very large closets and plenty of extra storage! Great location! Swedish Institute across the street, easy to show! Under ground heated parking available! Valet available 24 hours. On bus line! Taxes are included in monthly fee. Amenities include guest apartment, beautiful lobby, meeting room, Secure building with 24 hour staff.

Recently sold: $258,425. Beautiful 1906 bungalow in South Minneapolis' unique Powderhorn neighborhood. The specifics: three second-floor bedrooms, original woodwork, hardwood floors throughout, and ripple glass windows; an updated kitchen (with a dishwasher), formal dining room, one full bath upstairs with claw foot tub, and half bath downstairs, two car garage, new high efficiency furnace and hot water heater, which keep costs low. 

Our sweet, sunny house is located on an extra-large lot, with big back and side yards and a newly installed patio. It has been well-loved by gardeners and includes many raised beds, fruit trees, established perennials ? and even a chicken coop. 

Our house is in the heart of one of Minneapolis? most artistic, diverse, progressive, and friendly neighborhoods. It is just four blocks from beautiful Powderhorn Park where we enjoy ice skating and sledding in the winter, and walks around the lake and picnics in the summer. Powderhorn is home to the May Day Parade and Festival, the Art Sled Rally, an annual art fair, Powderhorn Empty Bowls, and Powderhorn Porchfest. We are right around the corner from a community-based art gallery and three blocks from Lake Street, Mercado Central, and In the Heart of the Beast Puppet and Mask Theater - and a quick walk across the park to the Midtown Global Market and Modern Times Café. The house is centrally located - a 10- minute commute to downtown Minneapolis, Saint Paul, Uptown or the U of M ? one block from multiple bus lines traveling throughout the city.
